## Key Takeaways

This project demonstrated how network packet analysis can be used to investigate phishing campaigns. Rather than relying only on the content of an email, I learned how SMTP metadata and packet-level evidence provide valuable information for tracing suspicious activity and supporting an investigation.

The experience also improved my confidence using Wireshark to inspect network traffic, apply protocol filters, and analyze communication between systems.

